fields.physical_description:
1.  box lid, card covered with dark blue paper; label stuck to the top and printed in black on white to show the title, maker's details and line drawings of children climbing steps.  It is badly damaged with tape sealing edges and corners and pencil and pen marks both on the outer and inner surfaces.
2.  box base, card covered with dark blue paper.  It is badly damaged with tape sealing edges and corners.
3.  box lining, grey plastic moulded to form ten compartments to hold the rods.  Across the centre is the title - CUISENAIRE NUMBERS IN COLOUR.  It is slightly damaged and the bottom edges splitting.
*The rods are blocks of wood of varying lengths and colours.  The basic measurements are 10cm square.

249-260.  tan, L. 100cm
fields.title: cuisenaire numbers in colours
fields.history_note:
References: Financial Times, January 1968.

These rods are based upon the Maria Montessori `Numbering Rods' , part of the set of didatic apparatus she designed to teach the child to measure without the use of aids other than the eye.
fields.production_note: Made by: The Cuisenaire Co Ltd, 40 Silver St., Reading, Berks.
